{
  "doc_id": "43327",
  "text": "Akhan et al. [CITATION_1] treated 12 hydatid cysts with the PAIR technique and draining catheters were used in four. The abscess occurred in four patients and two of them underwent splenectomy. The hospital stay ranged between 1 and 18 days [CITATION_2] . In another study, 12 patients with 20 splenic hydatid cysts were treated with the PAIR technique and seven of them used a draining catheter. The mean hospital stay was 2.3 days. The abscess was found in 16.6% of the patients [CITATION_3] .",
